    "Their methodology includes basic data preprocessing, feature extraction using VGG16FT and LSTM-RNNs, and classification with SVM.",
    "This approach incorporates the detailed morphology available from 3D fossils, offering new avenues for the study of three dimensional paleontological data.",
    "The ADMorph dataset is high-quality, suggesting high model sensitivity, effective training and good accuracy.",
    "Challenges in the future development of this approach include distinguishing between a broader range of taxa, especially where those incorporate a larger number of closely related species (a task with which the model struggled in this initial application).",
    "Mimura et al. (2022) introduce an innovative approach for detecting and classifying ichthyoliths (fossil fish teeth), within microscopic slide images."
